<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,440,675]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,482,508]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[747,771,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles ahead of rear shield margin, directed centrally, anterior lobe present; opisthosoma with 3 ridges, middorsal ridge fading simultaneously with subdorsal ridges; empodium entire; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,440,675]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
This genus consists of 151 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[656,898,607,633]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[759,815,608,633]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only 8 of these have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
